 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-ova","title":"Integrate circuit breaker with worker selection","description":"## Parent Epic: Circuit Breaker Pattern (remote_compilation_helper-9pw)

## Task Description

Modify the worker selection algorithm to exclude workers with open circuits. Workers in HalfOpen state should also be excluded from normal selection (they're only used for probing).

## Current State

In `rchd/src/selection.rs`:
```rust
pub async fn select_worker(
    pool: &WorkerPool,
    request: &SelectionRequest,
    weights: &SelectionWeights,
) -> Option<Arc<WorkerState>> {
    let healthy = pool.healthy_workers().await;
    // ... scoring and selection
}
```

The current implementation filters by WorkerStatus (Healthy, Degraded) but doesn't consider circuit state.

## Changes Required

### 1. Add Circuit State Access

Need a way for selection to query circuit state. Options:
- Store circuit state in WorkerState (simplest)
- Pass HealthMonitor reference to selection (coupling)
- Create shared circuit state registry (cleaner)

Recommended: Store circuit state in WorkerState for simplicity.

```rust
// In workers.rs
pub struct WorkerState {
    pub config: WorkerConfig,
    status: RwLock<WorkerStatus>,
    used_slots: AtomicU32,
    pub speed_score: f64,
    pub cached_projects: Vec<String>,
    circuit_state: RwLock<CircuitState>,  // NEW
}

impl WorkerState {
    pub async fn circuit_state(&self) -> CircuitState {
        self.circuit_state.read().await.clone()
    }

    pub async fn set_circuit_state(&self, state: CircuitState) {
        *self.circuit_state.write().await = state;
    }

    /// Check if worker is available for selection (healthy + circuit closed)
    pub async fn is_available(&self) -> bool {
        let status = self.status().await;
        let circuit = self.circuit_state().await;

        matches!(status, WorkerStatus::Healthy | WorkerStatus::Degraded)
            && circuit.is_closed()
    }
}
```

### 2. Update Selection Logic
```rust
pub async fn select_worker(
    pool: &WorkerPool,
    request: &SelectionRequest,
    weights: &SelectionWeights,
) -> SelectionResponse {
    // Get all workers
    let all_workers = pool.all_workers().await;

    if all_workers.is_empty() {
        return SelectionResponse::no_worker(SelectionReason::NoWorkersConfigured);
    }

    // Filter to available workers (healthy/degraded + circuit closed)
    let mut available = Vec::new();
    let mut all_circuits_open = true;
    let mut all_unreachable = true;

    for worker in all_workers {
        let status = worker.status().await;
        let circuit = worker.circuit_state().await;

        if !matches!(status, WorkerStatus::Unreachable | WorkerStatus::Disabled) {
            all_unreachable = false;
        }

        if circuit.is_closed() {
            all_circuits_open = false;
            if matches!(status, WorkerStatus::Healthy | WorkerStatus::Degraded) {
                available.push(worker);
            }
        }
    }

    if available.is_empty() {
        let reason = if all_unreachable {
            SelectionReason::AllWorkersUnreachable
        } else if all_circuits_open {
            SelectionReason::AllCircuitsOpen
        } else {
            SelectionReason::AllWorkersBusy
        };
        return SelectionResponse::no_worker(reason);
    }

    // Filter by slot availability
    let with_slots: Vec<_> = available
        .into_iter()
        .filter(|w| w.available_slots() >= request.required_cores)
        .collect();

    if with_slots.is_empty() {
        return SelectionResponse::no_worker(SelectionReason::AllWorkersBusy);
    }

    // Score and select best worker
    let scored: Vec<_> = with_slots
        .into_iter()
        .map(|w| {
            let score = calculate_score(&w, request, weights);
            (w, score)
        })
        .collect();

    let best = scored
        .into_iter()
        .max_by(|a, b| a.1.partial_cmp(&b.1).unwrap())
        .map(|(w, _)| w);

    // ... rest of selection
}
```

